---
import ServicePage from '../layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<ServicePage
  title="Link Building & Off-Page SEO | MM SEO"
  description="Ethical, sustainable link building from a freelance SEO consultant with 18 years of proven results. Quality backlinks that build authority and rankings. Manchester & UK."
  canonical="https://www.mmseo.co.uk/off-page-seo/"
  breadcrumb="Link Building"
>

  <!-- ── 1. Hero band (dark) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-hero-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Link Building &amp; Off-Page SEO | UK</p>
      <h1 class="sp-h1">Link Building: Earning Authority, Not Buying It</h1>
      <p class="sp-intro">
        Backlinks remain one of Google's most important ranking signals. But the kind
        of links that move rankings and stand the test of algorithm updates are the
        ones earned through genuine relevance and value, not bought in bulk from
        link farms. I build the kind of authority that compounds over time.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Main content (light) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">Why Backlinks Still Matter</h2>

      <p>
        Google's algorithm has evolved enormously over the past decade, but links
        remain a fundamental trust signal. When authoritative, relevant websites link
        to yours, it tells Google that your content is credible and worth surfacing.
        The sites with the strongest, most relevant link profiles consistently outrank
        those without them, even when on-page and technical factors are equal.
      </p>
      <p>
        The quality and relevance of links matters far more than quantity. A single
        editorial mention in a well-regarded industry publication is worth more than
        hundreds of directory listings. My approach is built around this reality.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3">My link building approach</h3>
      <ul class="sp-list">
        <li><strong>Digital PR</strong>: creating genuinely newsworthy content or data assets that earn coverage from journalists and publishers</li>
        <li><strong>Blogger &amp; editorial outreach</strong>: identifying and building relationships with relevant bloggers, writers, and site owners in your niche</li>
        <li><strong>Content-led acquisition</strong>: producing linkable assets (guides, tools, research, statistics pages) that attract organic links</li>
        <li><strong>Broken link building</strong>: finding broken outbound links on relevant sites and offering your content as a replacement</li>
        <li><strong>Competitor backlink analysis</strong>: identifying sites that link to your competitors and building a case for why they should link to you</li>
        <li><strong>Business &amp; industry directories</strong>: high-quality, curated directory submissions that contribute to NAP consistency and local authority</li>
        <li><strong>Unlinked brand mentions</strong>: converting existing online mentions of your business into editorial backlinks</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Why it matters (dark) ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Ethical Link Building: What That Actually Means</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        "White hat" and "ethical" are terms that get thrown around loosely in SEO.
        What they mean in practice is building links that Google would be comfortable
        knowing about: editorial mentions, genuine outreach, and content that earns
        its place. Not private blog networks, not paid placements disguised as editorial,
        not reciprocal link exchanges that exist solely to game the algorithm.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        The risk with low-quality link building isn't just that it won't work. It
        that it can actively damage your site's authority and trigger manual penalties.
        I've helped clients recover from exactly this situation. Prevention is
        considerably cheaper than the cure.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Honest expectations matter here too. Link building takes time. The results
        of a link acquisition campaign typically begin to show in rankings after
        3–6 months, as Google processes and weighs new links. I'll give you a
        realistic projection based on your niche, your current authority, and the
        competitiveness of your target terms.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Relevant result (light) ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-result section-light">
    <div class="container sp-result-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow dark-eyebrow">Proven Results</p>
      <blockquote class="sp-quote">
        <p class="sp-quote-metric">+125% organic traffic · +552% organic revenue</p>
        <p class="sp-quote-context">
          A targeted blogger outreach and link acquisition campaign, running alongside
          technical fixes and content work, helped Illuminated Mirrors build the
          authority their competitors had accumulated over years. The result was
          125% organic traffic growth and 552% organic revenue growth within six months.
        </p>
        <footer class="sp-quote-credit">— Illuminated Mirrors (eCommerce · UK)</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 5. Related Services ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="related-services section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Related Services</p>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/technical-seo/" class="related-card">
          <strong>Technical SEO</strong>
          <span>Backlinks work harder when your site's technical foundations are solid.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/keyword-research/" class="related-card">
          <strong>Keyword Research</strong>
          <span>Know which pages deserve links and which searches they should target.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/seo-strategy/" class="related-card">
          <strong>SEO Strategy</strong>
          <span>Integrate link building into a wider SEO plan that drives lasting growth.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 6. Contact CTA ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <ContactForm />

</ServicePage>

<style>
  .section-dark  { background-color: var(--ink);  color: var(--chalk); }
  .section-light { background-color: var(--chalk); color: var(--ink); }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem);
  }

  .sp-hero { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
  .sp-hero-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .dark-eyebrow { color: var(--accent); }

  .sp-h1 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background-color: var(--accent-dk); }

  .sp-content { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-content-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-h2 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-h2.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .sp-h3 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .sp-content p, .sp-content-inner p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }

  .sp-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }
  .sp-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .sp-why { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-why-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .chalk { color: var(--chalk); }
  .chalk-muted {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
  }

  .sp-result { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-result-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background-color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.04);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-quote-metric {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-context {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.75);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-credit {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }

  .related-services { padding: 3rem 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) { .related-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
  .related-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }
  .related-card:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-color: rgba(255,104,38,0.4); }
  .related-card strong { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: #F8F7F2; font-weight: 600; }
  .related-card span { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: rgba(248,247,242,0.5); line-height: 1.55; }
</style>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.12 }
  );
  revealEls.forEach(el => io.observe(el));
</script>
